                <h1>Do You Need to Unfreeze Credit for a Background Check?</h1>
                <p>Yes, you typically need to unfreeze your credit for a background check, especially if the check involves a credit report. Employers and landlords often rely on this information to make decisions. Unfreezing your credit ensures they can access your report without delays or issues. Be sure to freeze it again after the check.</p>
